The paper deals with the problem of aggregating data in a dynamic graph, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The use of pairwise interactions and the consideration of different adversaries suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational complexity, which could place it in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Algorithms (cs.AL).
